  "text": "Cases of urticaria, asthma, rhinitis, or anaphylactic shock have been reported following oral, dermal, or inhalation exposure to benzoic acid. The symptoms appear shortly even at low doses and disappear within a few hours. Information regarding skin reactions caused by benzoic acid in the general population is limited [CITATION_1] .",
